comments.content: [Sackers Heavy Gothic](http://web.archive.org/web/20150306061409/http:/www.fontshop.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=catalog.fontdetail&displayfontid=C.2781.4.19&attributes.sampleSize=48&sampleText=ACQUA+di+PARMA&sampleSize=48) and [Proxima Nova](http://web.archive.org/web/20150306061409/http:/www.fontshop.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=catalog.fontdetail&displayfontid=MSF.123353.0.7&attributes.sampleSize=48&sampleText=ACQUA+DI+PARMA&sampleSize=48) will get you close. The spacing of the logo leads me to believe it was hand drawn or metal set long ago.
